<div class="heading resPageHeading">


























<h1 >Tips for creating accessible websites</h1></div>

<div class="content stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="dbb2ea9e-a541-4414-97e2-2ae4a3b22e04" >

    <p>Web accessibility is the practice of removing barriers and creating equal access to information and websites for people with disabilities. It is aimed to address barriers relating to visual, motor, auditory, and cognitive disabilities. For example, individuals who are blind use screen reading software that reads content using a synthesized voice. Someone who has a physical disability that affects their use of hands or are unable to use a mouse may rely exclusively on a keyboard. How a website or application is designed can significantly impact a user's experience, therefore how we design or structure a website is important.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#dbb2ea9e-a541-4414-97e2-2ae4a3b22e04");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-opaque" id="32719789-4091-4984-949e-b5319bebf72c" >

    <p><strong>On this page:</strong></p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a href="#headings">Heading structure</a></li> 
 <li><a href="#links">Self-describing page links</a></li> 
 <li><a href="#skip-nav">Skip navigation links</a></li> 
 <li><a href="#colour">How to use colour</a></li> 
 <li><a href="#contrast">Contrast</a></li> 
 <li><a href="#alternative-text">Alternative text for images</a></li> 
 <li><a href="#forms">Forms and labels</a></li> 
 <li><a href="#tables">Tables</a></li> 
 <li><a href="#testing">Test the accessibility of a website</a></li> 
 <li><a href="#further-reading">Further reading</a></li> 
 <li><a href="#featured">Featured resources</a></li> 
</ul>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#32719789-4091-4984-949e-b5319bebf72c");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="303eb643-f3e5-43f5-bb92-828700eabcdb" >

    <h2><a name="headings"></a>Heading structure</h2> 
<p>HTML headings do not only act as visual cues, but also as an outline as to how a page is structured and how sections relate to one another. Proper heading structure can be especially useful for people who use screen readers, as they can be used as a navigational aids to jump from heading to heading.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Make sure headings (H1, H2, H3...) are structured in a logical order that conveys hierarchy, ensuring that all headings have a proper parent/child relationship.</li> 
 <li>It’s best practice to start each page with a single Heading 1 in the main content area. Heading 1 is the most important heading in terms of rank or hierarchy.</li> 
 <li>Different levels of subheadings should be underneath main headings, for example a H3 would be nested under a H2. Skipping heading ranks can be confusing and should be avoided.</li> 
</ul>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#303eb643-f3e5-43f5-bb92-828700eabcdb");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="2a70d398-0766-4522-99b6-884545e6c25a" >

    <h2><a name="links"></a>Self-describing page links</h2> 
<p>Ensure hyperlinks are self-describing. “Click here” or "learn more" does not provide any useful information to someone using a screen reader, and does not make sense out of context. For best practice, hyperlinks should be descriptive, link to nouns that are specific in context, and try to be placed towards the end of a sentence.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#2a70d398-0766-4522-99b6-884545e6c25a");});</script></div>

				

				
