<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="83e54dd2-e58a-4880-8369-003850bcfa35" >

    <h2><a name="tables"></a>Tables</h2> 
<p>Tables should be used to present data in tabular form. Accessible tables should include proper HTML markup.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Use table headers (&lt;th&gt; element) to markup all column or row headers.</li> 
 <li>Define the scope of each header, indicating whether it’s a column or row header. The value of the scope attribute can either be “col” or “row”.</li> 
 <li>Avoid merged cells and empty table headers if possible.</li> 
</ul>
    





</div>
